
### 2. `.gitignore` File

This file will specify which files and directories Git should ignore. Here's a basic `.gitignore` for a Python project:

```gitignore
# Byte-compiled files
*.pyc
*.pyo
*.pyd
__pycache__/

# Virtual environment
venv/
.env/

# Distribution and packaging
build/
dist/
*.egg-info/
*.egg

# IDEs and editors
.vscode/
.idea/
*.sublime-project
*.sublime-workspace

# System files
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Pyenv
.python-version

# Pylint
pylint.report

# Other files
*.log
